            <h2>Events</h2>
            <p>Here you will find details of special events and activities coming up at Cathcart United Free Church
            and in our wider community. For our regular weekly meetings please see the
            <a href="/meetings">Meetings page</a>.</p>
            <!-- JUNE 2026 -->
            <h3 class="event-month">June 2026</h3>
            <div class="event-list">
                <div class="event-card">
                    <p class="event-meta">Saturday 6th June &bull; 8:30–10am &bull; Cathcart United Free Church</p>
                    <h3>Prayer Breakfast</h3>
                    <p>Our monthly joint Prayer Breakfast with Cathcart Church of Scotland and Cathcart Baptist Church.
                    Breakfast is served from 8:30–9am followed by a time of prayer together around a theme. Topic TBA.</p>
                    <p>All are welcome.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="event-card">
                    <p class="event-meta">Saturday 6th June &bull; 10:30am–12pm &bull; Cathcart United Free Church</p>
                    <h3>Off the CUF</h3>
                    <p>Our monthly café-style gathering exploring a theme that speaks to our shared human experience.
                    Food, Friendship and Faith — free and open to all. Children welcome, under the responsibility
                    of a parent or carer.</p>
                    <p><a href="/church-life/off-the-cuf" class="section-link">Find out more about Off the CUF →</a></p>
                </div>
                <div class="event-card">
                    <p class="event-meta">Sunday 28th June &bull; 11am &bull; Cathcart United Free Church</p>
                    <h3>Love Your Church — Sunday Service</h3>
                    <p>We continue our series looking at the early church in Acts 1–12. This Sunday we will be
                    exploring the second chapter of the book <em>Love Your Church</em> by Tony Merida — what it
                    means to be a welcoming church.</p>
                    <p>Over the coming months we are encouraging people to read the book and discuss it with others.
                    Once a month in the Sunday morning service we'll take up one of the eight themes:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Belonging (26th April) ✓</li>
                        <li>Welcoming (31st May) ✓</li>
                        <li><strong>Gathering</strong></li>
                        <li>Caring</li>
                        <li>Service</li>
                        <li>Honouring</li>
                        <li>Witnessing</li>
                        <li>Sending</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

